|format=[[Ogg]]
}}
The lead single of album was "Ven Conmigo (Solamente T<U+00FA>)", the Spanish version of "[[Come On Over Baby (All I Want Is You)]]", which was released on August 8, 2000 to Latin radio stations.<ref name="debut">{{cite journal|url=http://books.google.com/books?id=fBAEAAAAMBAJ&pg=PA85&dq=intitle:billboard+%22ven+conmigo%22+%22reflejo%22&hl=en&sa=X&ei=y5t9UZjGHoa08QT6noGgAw&ved=0CEYQ6AEwBA#v=onepage&q=intitle%3Abillboard%20%22ven%20conmigo%22%20%22reflejo%22&f=false|title=Aguilera Makes Spanish Debut On BMG U.S. Latin|last=Cobo|first=Leila|work=Billboard|publisher=Prometheus Global Media|volume=112|issue=33|page=85|date=August 12, 2000|accessdate=April 28, 2013}}</ref> The song reached number-one on the [[Hot Latin Songs|''Billboard'' Hot Latin Songs]] and number two on the [[Latin Pop Songs|''Billboard'' Latin Pop Songs]] charts.<ref name="latinsongs">{{cite web|url={{BillboardURLbyName|artist=christina aguilera|chart=Latin Songs C}}|title=Christina Aguilera - Chart history: Latin Songs|work=Billboard|publisher=Prometheus Global Media|accessdate=May 1, 2013}}</ref><ref name="latinpopsongs">{{cite web|url={{BillboardURLbyName|artist=christina aguilera|chart=Latin Pop Songs C}}|title=Christina Aguilera - Chart history: Latin Pop Songs|work=Billboard|publisher=Prometheus Global Media|accessdate=May 1, 2013}}</ref> It also peaked at number eight in Spain.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.spanishcharts.com/showitem.asp?interpret=Christina+Aguilera&titel=Ven+conmigo+%28solamente+t%FA%29&cat=s|title=Christina - Ven conmigo (solamente t<U+00FA>)|work=[[PROMUSICAE]]|language=Spanish|publisher=Hung Media|date=September 12, 2000|accessdate=May 1, 2013}}</ref> The second single, "[[Pero Me Acuerdo de Ti]]" was released in December 2000.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://books.google.com/books?id=TxEEAAAAMBAJ&pg=PA36&dq=intitle:billboard+%22pero+me+acuerdo+de+ti%22&hl=en&sa=X&ei=XA1-UZ7SJIm49gTm8oGQDg&ved=0CDkQ6AEwAQ#v=onepage&q&f=false|title=Christina On Top|last=Cobo|first=Leila|work=Billboard|publisher=Prometheus Global Media|date=December 23, 2000|accessdate=April 29, 2013|volume=112|issue=52|page=35}}</ref> The song reached number eight on the Hot Latin Songs and number five on Latin Pop Songs charts.<ref name="latinsongs"/><ref name="latinpopsongs"/> In Spain, it reached number three on the chart.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.spanishcharts.com/showitem.asp?interpret=Christina+Aguilera&titel=Pero+me+acuerdo+de+ti&cat=s|title=Christina Aguilera - Pero me acuerdo de ti|work=PROMUSICAE|publisher=Hung Media|date=March 10, 2001|accessdate=May 1, 2013}}</ref> Its music video was directed by Kevin G. Bray.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.mtv.com/videos/christina-aguilera/805268/pero-me-acuerdo-de-ti.jhtml |title=Christina Aguilera - Music Videos |publisher=[[MTV Networks]] |accessdate=December 4, 2012}}</ref> The third single "[[Falsas Esperanzas]]" was released on July 3, 2001.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.allmusic.com/album/falsas-esperanzas-mw0000379519|title=Falsas Esperanzas: Overview|work=Allmusic|publisher=Rovi|accessdate=April 29, 2013}}</ref> The song reached number fifteen in Spain.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.spanishcharts.com/showitem.asp?interpret=Christina+Aguilera&titel=Falsas+esperanzas&cat=s|title=Christina Aguilera - Falsas esperanzas|work=PROMUSICAE|publisher=Hung Media|date=June 9, 2001|accessdate=May 1, 2013}}</ref> Its music video, taken from her DVD ''[[My Reflection]]'', was directed by Lawrence Jordan.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.mtv.com/videos/christina-aguilera/805309/falsas-esperanzas.jhtml#artist=509026 |title=Christina Aguilera " Music Videos |publisher=[[MTV Networks]] |accessdate=December 4, 2012}}</ref> "Genio Atrapado" and "Por Siempre Tu" were previously released as singles along with their original versions.<ref name="enespanol"/><ref>{{cite journal|url=http://books.google.com/books?id=rg8EAAAAMBAJ&pg=PA125&dq=intitle:billboard+%22por+siempre+tu%22&hl=en&sa=X&ei=tsGAUd6pKYiy8ATLsoC4Bg&ved=0CHAQ6AEwDw#v=onepage&q&f=false|title=Hot 100 Spotlight|last=Pietroluongo|first=Silvio|work=Billboard|publisher=Prometheus Global Media|date=June 24, 2000|accessdate=May 1, 2013|volume=112|issue=26|page=125}}</ref> The former single peaked at number thirteen on the [[Hot Latin Songs|''Billboard'' Hot Latin Songs]] chart while the latter single peaked at number six on the Hot Latin Songs and number two on the [[Latin Pop Songs|''Billboard'' Latin Pop Songs]] chart.<ref name="latinsongs"/><ref name="latinpopsongs"/>

==Promotion==
{{Main|Christina Aguilera: In Concert}}

To promote ''Mi Reflejo'', Aguilera extended her tour, [[Christina Aguilera: In Concert]], into 2001 for eight more dates, visiting Mexico, Puerto Rico, Venezuela, Panama and Japan.<ref name="seattle">{{cite web |url=http://seattlepi.nwsource.com/pop/chrs20.shtml |title=Polished Aguilera gives fans what they want and more |last=Stout|first=Gene |date=October 20, 2000 |work=[[Seattle Post-Intelligencer]] |publisher=[[Hearst Corporation]] |accessdate=December 29, 2011|archiveurl=http://web.archive.org/web/20020525032554/http://seattlepi.nwsource.com/pop/chrs20.shtml |archivedate=May 25, 2002}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://mensual.prensa.com/mensual/contenido/2001/01/23/uhora.htm#top |title=Unas 20 mil personas fueron al concierto de Christina Aguilera|language=Spanish|author= |date= January 23, 2001 |work=La Prensa |publisher=Corporaci<U+00F3>n La Prensa |accessdate=December 29, 2011|archiveurl= http://www.freezepage.com/1325158284CTXSMCNGIO|archivedate=December 29, 2011}}</ref> Aguilera also gave a performance at the [[2001 Grammy Awards]], performing "Pero Me Acuerdo de Ti" and "Falsas Esperanzas".<ref>{{cite web| url=http://www.mtv.com/bands/g/news_feature_grammyflashback/2001/ | title=Grammys 2001|work=[[MTV]]|publisher=[[Viacom Media Networks]]|accessdate=April 30, 2013}}</ref>

==Accolades==
At the [[Latin Grammy Awards of 2001]], the album received the award for [[Latin Grammy Award for Best Female Pop Vocal Album|Best Female Pop Vocal Album]].<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.rollingstone.com/music/news/christina-wins-latin-grammy-20011030|title=Christina Wins Latin Grammy|last=Saraceno|first=Christina|work=[[Rolling Stone]]|publisher=[[Wenner Media LLC]]|date=July 18, 2001|accessdate=April 29, 2013}}</ref> At the [[2001 Grammy Awards]], the album received a nomination for [[Grammy Award for Best Latin Pop Album|Best Latin Pop Album]] which was awarded to Shakira for ''[[MTV Unplugged (Shakira album)|MTV Unplugged]]''.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://edition.cnn.com/2001/SHOWBIZ/Music/02/21/grammy.winners/|title=43rd Grammy Awards|work=[[CNN]]|publisher=[[Time Warner]]|date=February 21, 2001|accessdate=May 1, 201}}</ref> The album also received a nomination at the [[Premio Lo Nuestro 2001|13th Lo Nuestro Awards]] for "[[Lo Nuestro Award for Pop Album of the Year|Pop Album of the Year]]", but lost to ''Paulina'' by Paulina Rubio.<ref name="noms-LN-2001">{{cite web |url=http://especiales.univision.com/contentuvn/rinconlatino/plnuestro/opinion.html|title=Premios Lo Nuestro: Votaci<U+00F3>n 2001|work=[[Univision]] |publisher=[[Univision Communications]]|accessdate=August 14, 2013|year=2001}}</ref> Aguilera herself received two Lo Nuestro awards including [[Lo Nuestro Award for Pop Female Artist of the Year|Pop Female Artist of the Year]] and [[Lo Nuestro Award for Pop New Artist of the Year|Pop New Artist of the Year]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Lo Nuestro: Ganadores 2001|url=http://www.univision.com/content/content.jhtml?cid=490992|accessdate=May 1, 2013|language=Spanish|work=[[Univision]]|publisher=[[Univision Communications]]}}</ref> At the 2001 [[Billboard Latin Music Awards]], the album received two awards for Pop Album of the Year by a Female Artist and Pop Album of the Year by a New Artist.<ref>{{cite journal|url=http://books.google.com/books?id=oxMEAAAAMBAJ&pg=PA56&dq=intitle:billboard+%22pop+album+of+the+year+female%22+%22reflejo%22&hl=en&sa=X&ei=3rDHUaLOKIPa9QSCuoHwCg&ved=0CDYQ6AEwAQ#v=onepage&q&f=false|title=Billboard Awards Recognize The Best In Latin Music|last=Cobo|first=Leila|work=Billboard|publisher=Prometheus Global Media|date=April 28, 2001|accessdate=April 29, 2013|volume=113|issue=17|page=56}}</ref> At the 2001 [[Blockbuster LLC|Blockbuster Entertainment Awards]], Aguilera received an award for Favorite Artist, Latino due to the success of the album in the United States.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.hollywood.com/static/2001-blockbuster-awards-winners-list-|title=2001 Blockbuster Awards Winners List|work=[[The Hollywood Reporter]]|publisher=Prometheus Global Media|accessdate=May 2, 2013}}</ref>

